    "Id": "911972",
    "ThreadId": "395339",
    "Html": "<p>I believe this is a limitation in Microsoft's configuration implementation. (I haven't verified this.) The reason we have that feature is so that advanced configuration setups where you have elements that have some things in common, and some things not in common, can have those common things in a superclass instead of having to add them multiple times on each of the elements.</p>",
